Reasoning: The paper deals with developing a data structure for answering substring minimal suffix queries in constant time after linear-time preprocessing. This involves the use of algorithmic and combinatorial tools such as Lyndon words, Lyndon factorizations, fusion trees, and order isomorphism of strings. These topics are closely related to the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS), formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL), information theory (cs.IT), social and information networks (cs.SI), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
